{"title_page": "Gay Star News", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Gay Star News\n| logo = Gay Star News Logo 2012.jpg\n| logo_size = 250px\n| type = Private\n| industry = Internet News\n| founder = Tris Reid-Smith (Director, Editor-in-Chief)<br />Scott Nunn (Director of Sales and Marketing){{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n| defunct = 2019\n| location_city = [[London]]\n| location_country = [[United Kingdom]]\n| founded = 2011\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.gaystarnews.com}}\n}}\n'''''Gay Star News''''' is a [[news website]] focused on events related to and concerning the global [[LGBTI]] community. All the articles cover events and issues affecting the world's [[lesbian]]s, [[gay]]s, [[bisexual]]s, [[transgender]] and [[intersex]]<ref name=\"Intersex\">{{cite web|url=http://oiiaustralia.com/21233/gaystarnews-tasmanian-intersex-discrimination-plans-hailed-as-world-first/|title=Intersex in Australia|date=21 October 2012|website=oiiaustralia.com|accessdate=21 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121115003926/http://oiiaustralia.com/21233/gaystarnews-tasmanian-intersex-discrimination-plans-hailed-as-world-first/|archive-date=15 November 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> people, published continuously and daily. This includes discussing which important figures in history were gay.<ref name=\"Da Vinci\">{{cite web|url=http://www.southfloridagaynews.com/news/world-news/7340-leonardo-da-vinci-named-most-powerful-gay-in-history.html|title=Da Vinci Gay|date=26 September 2011|publisher=southfloridagaynews.com|accessdate=26 September 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119184443/http://www.southfloridagaynews.com/news/world-news/7340-leonardo-da-vinci-named-most-powerful-gay-in-history.html|archive-date=19 November 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=February 2018}}\n\nHeadquartered in the UK, it is privately owned and was founded by Tris Reid-Smith and Scott Nunn in December, 2011.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nThe site reports on [[breaking news]] in international politics, religion, business, crime, entertainment and lifestyle, presenting the information without offering analyses or opinions on events and interviews. The site also features interviews with members of the LGBTI community.<ref name=\"LGBT Profiles\">{{cite web|url=http://www.truthwinsout.org/blog/2012/10/30261/|title=GSN Profiles Wayne Besen|website=truthwinsout.org|date=5 October 2012|accessdate=5 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009061517/http://www.truthwinsout.org/blog/2012/10/30261/|archive-date=9 October 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>  A permanent staff of internationally based professional reporters handles day-to-day story coverage{{citation needed|date=February 2018}} but the site also includes articles by LGBTI activists, freelancers, bloggers, academics, historians, celebrities and people of prominence.\n\nThe site features 'top stories', 'entertainment', 'features', 'travel', 'GSN loves' and 'comment', 'Business', 'Family, 'Support' and 'Prides and Festivals' sections. Readers could post comments, share and like stories to display on online [[social network]]s including [[Facebook]], [[Instagram]], [[Twitter]], [[YouTube]], [[Sina Weibo|Weibo]] and [[LinkedIn]].\n\nOn 30 July 2019, ''Gay Star News'' announced that it would be shutting down after almost eight years because of falling revenues due to an inability to monetize.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Reid-Smith |first1=Tris |title=Gay Star News is closing: You deserve the full story, all our thanks and love |url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-star-news-is-closing-you-deserve-the-full-story-all-our-thanks-and-love/ |website=Gay Star News |accessdate=2020-04-05 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804211035/https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-star-news-is-closing-you-deserve-the-full-story-all-our-thanks-and-love/ |archivedate=2019-08-04 |date=30 July 2019 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.queerty.com/without-warning-major-lgbtq-media-site-announces-shutting-effective-immediately-20190730|title=Without any warning, major LGBTQ media site announces it\u2019s shutting down effective immediately|last=Gremore|first=Graham|date=2019-07-30|website=www.queerty.com|access-date=2019-07-30 }}</ref>  However, following acquisition of the intellectual property of Gay Star News by Iconic Labs,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Warrington |first1=James |title=Media firm Iconic Labs buys Gay Star News for \u00a31 |url=https://www.cityam.com/media-firm-iconic-labs-buys-gay-star-news-for-1/ |website=[[City A.M.]] |accessdate=2020-04-05 |date=9 September 2019}}</ref> publication of Gay Star News has resumed.\n\n== History ==\n''Gay Star News'' went live with the backing of investors: [[Goldman Sachs]], [[PricewaterhouseCoopers|PwC]] and National Australia Bank<ref>{{cite news|last=Reid-Smith|first=Tris|title=The story of GayStarNews|url=http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/complete-quick-story-gay-star-news051012|accessdate=23 January 2014|newspaper=GayStarNews.com|date=5 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202160152/http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/complete-quick-story-gay-star-news051012|archive-date=2 February 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> on 16 January 2012. [[Stephen Fry]] then tweeted his support to his 3.7 million followers, and is credited by ''Gay Star News'' for publicising their site regularly.<ref name=\"Fry tweet\">{{cite web|title=Stephen Fry tweet on day one|url=http://2012.bluedropawards.org/best-media-website-built-with-drupal/nominees/gay-star-news|publisher=BlueDropAwards.org|accessdate=23 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201224904/http://2012.bluedropawards.org/best-media-website-built-with-drupal/nominees/gay-star-news|archive-date=1 February 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012 the site won the [[Stonewall (charity)|Stonewall UK]] Award for Publication of the Year.<ref name=\"Stonewall Award\">{{cite web|url=http://www.stonewall.org.uk/what_you_can_do/events/2595.asp|title=Stonewall Awards Winners|publisher=stonewall.org.uk|date=1 November 2012|accessdate=5 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316224728/http://stonewall.org.uk/what_you_can_do/events/2595.asp|archive-date=16 March 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=February 2018}}{{Verify source|date=February 2018}}\n\nThe editorial policy of ''Gay Star News'' is to publish pro-LGBTI media without [[activism]]. Commonly seen advertisers on the site are: [[International Fund for Animal Welfare]], Direct Line insurance, Lufthansa Airways,<ref name=\"Fry tweet\"/> Travelex, Lloyds Bank, Smirnoff, Blued, Manchester United, late night rooms, Alfa Romeo, Heathrow, [[Snickers]], Hoseasons, naked wines, npower, Fujitsu, the co-operative, the [[London Women's Clinic]], Knight Frank, DigitasLBI and several pride support groups.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nIn 2016 Gay Star News launched [http://www.digitalpride.com/ Digital Pride]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://outnewsglobal.com/2934-2/|title=Digital Pride launches in April 2016 - Out News Global|website=outnewsglobal.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616231322/http://outnewsglobal.com/2934-2/|archive-date=2018-06-16|url-status=live}}</ref> - an annual, week-long program of online discussions, articles and video events to promote LGBTI Pride around the world - particularly to those in countries facing oppression.\n\nIn 2017, it ran a hard-hitting series of articles on \u2018chemsex\u2019 - a slang reference for the way some gay and bisexual men indulge in drug taking and sexual activity.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2017/09/15/men-being-raped-at-chemsex-parties-are-too-afraid-to-go-to-the-police-6928504/|title=Men being raped at chemsex parties are too afraid to go to the police|date=2017-09-15|work=Metro|access-date=2018-06-16|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617015316/https://metro.co.uk/2017/09/15/men-being-raped-at-chemsex-parties-are-too-afraid-to-go-to-the-police-6928504/|archive-date=2018-06-17|url-status=live}}</ref> This included research into the prevalence of the practice and the negative impact on some men\u2019s lives.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.winq.com/2017/09/survey-gay-bi-men-reveals-shocking-truth-chemsex/|title=Survey of gay and bi men reveals the shocking truth about chemsex - winq.|date=2017-09-15|work=winq.|access-date=2018-06-16|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190105012424/http://www.winq.com/2017/09/survey-gay-bi-men-reveals-shocking-truth-chemsex/|archive-date=2019-01-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n[[Category:2011 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related media in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related websites]]\n[[Category:British news websites]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Gay Star News\n| logo = Gay Star News Logo 2012.jpg\n| logo_size = 250px\n| type = Private\n| industry = Internet News\n| founder = Tris Reid-Smith (Director, Editor-in-Chief)<br />Scott Nunn (Director of Sales and Marketing){{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n| defunct = 2019\n| location_city = [[London]]\n| location_country = [[United Kingdom]]\n| founded = 2011\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.gaystarnews.com}}\n}}\n'''''Gay Star News''''' was a [[news website]] focused on events related to and concerning the global [[LGBTI]] community. All the articles cover events and issues affecting the world's [[lesbian]]s, [[gay]]s, [[bisexual]]s, [[transgender]] and [[intersex]]<ref name=\"Intersex\">{{cite web|url=http://oiiaustralia.com/21233/gaystarnews-tasmanian-intersex-discrimination-plans-hailed-as-world-first/|title=Intersex in Australia|date=21 October 2012|website=oiiaustralia.com|accessdate=21 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121115003926/http://oiiaustralia.com/21233/gaystarnews-tasmanian-intersex-discrimination-plans-hailed-as-world-first/|archive-date=15 November 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> people, published continuously and daily. This includes discussing which important figures in history were gay.<ref name=\"Da Vinci\">{{cite web|url=http://www.southfloridagaynews.com/news/world-news/7340-leonardo-da-vinci-named-most-powerful-gay-in-history.html|title=Da Vinci Gay|date=26 September 2011|publisher=southfloridagaynews.com|accessdate=26 September 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119184443/http://www.southfloridagaynews.com/news/world-news/7340-leonardo-da-vinci-named-most-powerful-gay-in-history.html|archive-date=19 November 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=February 2018}}\n\nHeadquartered in the UK, it is privately owned and was founded by Tris Reid-Smith and Scott Nunn in December, 2011.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nThe site reports on [[breaking news]] in international politics, religion, business, crime, entertainment and lifestyle, presenting the information without offering analyses or opinions on events and interviews. The site also features interviews with members of the LGBTI community.<ref name=\"LGBT Profiles\">{{cite web|url=http://www.truthwinsout.org/blog/2012/10/30261/|title=GSN Profiles Wayne Besen|website=truthwinsout.org|date=5 October 2012|accessdate=5 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009061517/http://www.truthwinsout.org/blog/2012/10/30261/|archive-date=9 October 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>  A permanent staff of internationally based professional reporters handles day-to-day story coverage{{citation needed|date=February 2018}} but the site also includes articles by LGBTI activists, freelancers, bloggers, academics, historians, celebrities and people of prominence.\n\nThe site features 'top stories', 'entertainment', 'features', 'travel', 'GSN loves' and 'comment', 'Business', 'Family, 'Support' and 'Prides and Festivals' sections. Readers could post comments, share and like stories to display on online [[social network]]s including [[Facebook]], [[Instagram]], [[Twitter]], [[YouTube]], [[Sina Weibo|Weibo]] and [[LinkedIn]].\n\nOn 30 July 2019, ''Gay Star News'' announced that it would be shutting down after almost eight years because of falling revenues due to an inability to monetize.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Reid-Smith |first1=Tris |title=Gay Star News is closing: You deserve the full story, all our thanks and love |url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-star-news-is-closing-you-deserve-the-full-story-all-our-thanks-and-love/ |website=Gay Star News |accessdate=2020-04-05 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804211035/https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-star-news-is-closing-you-deserve-the-full-story-all-our-thanks-and-love/ |archivedate=2019-08-04 |date=30 July 2019 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.queerty.com/without-warning-major-lgbtq-media-site-announces-shutting-effective-immediately-20190730|title=Without any warning, major LGBTQ media site announces it\u2019s shutting down effective immediately|last=Gremore|first=Graham|date=2019-07-30|website=www.queerty.com|access-date=2019-07-30 }}</ref>  However, following acquisition of the intellectual property of Gay Star News by Iconic Labs,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Warrington |first1=James |title=Media firm Iconic Labs buys Gay Star News for \u00a31 |url=https://www.cityam.com/media-firm-iconic-labs-buys-gay-star-news-for-1/ |website=[[City A.M.]] |accessdate=2020-04-05 |date=9 September 2019}}</ref> publication of Gay Star News has resumed.\n\n== History ==\n''Gay Star News'' went live with the backing of investors: [[Goldman Sachs]], [[PricewaterhouseCoopers|PwC]] and National Australia Bank<ref>{{cite news|last=Reid-Smith|first=Tris|title=The story of GayStarNews|url=http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/complete-quick-story-gay-star-news051012|accessdate=23 January 2014|newspaper=GayStarNews.com|date=5 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202160152/http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/complete-quick-story-gay-star-news051012|archive-date=2 February 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> on 16 January 2012. [[Stephen Fry]] then tweeted his support to his 3.7 million followers, and is credited by ''Gay Star News'' for publicising their site regularly.<ref name=\"Fry tweet\">{{cite web|title=Stephen Fry tweet on day one|url=http://2012.bluedropawards.org/best-media-website-built-with-drupal/nominees/gay-star-news|publisher=BlueDropAwards.org|accessdate=23 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201224904/http://2012.bluedropawards.org/best-media-website-built-with-drupal/nominees/gay-star-news|archive-date=1 February 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012 the site won the [[Stonewall (charity)|Stonewall UK]] Award for Publication of the Year.<ref name=\"Stonewall Award\">{{cite web|url=http://www.stonewall.org.uk/what_you_can_do/events/2595.asp|title=Stonewall Awards Winners|publisher=stonewall.org.uk|date=1 November 2012|accessdate=5 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316224728/http://stonewall.org.uk/what_you_can_do/events/2595.asp|archive-date=16 March 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=February 2018}}{{Verify source|date=February 2018}}\n\nThe editorial policy of ''Gay Star News'' is to publish pro-LGBTI media without [[activism]]. Commonly seen advertisers on the site are: [[International Fund for Animal Welfare]], Direct Line insurance, Lufthansa Airways,<ref name=\"Fry tweet\"/> Travelex, Lloyds Bank, Smirnoff, Blued, Manchester United, late night rooms, Alfa Romeo, Heathrow, [[Snickers]], Hoseasons, naked wines, npower, Fujitsu, the co-operative, the [[London Women's Clinic]], Knight Frank, DigitasLBI and several pride support groups.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nIn 2016 Gay Star News launched [http://www.digitalpride.com/ Digital Pride]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://outnewsglobal.com/2934-2/|title=Digital Pride launches in April 2016 - Out News Global|website=outnewsglobal.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616231322/http://outnewsglobal.com/2934-2/|archive-date=2018-06-16|url-status=live}}</ref> - an annual, week-long program of online discussions, articles and video events to promote LGBTI Pride around the world - particularly to those in countries facing oppression.\n\nIn 2017, it ran a hard-hitting series of articles on \u2018chemsex\u2019 - a slang reference for the way some gay and bisexual men indulge in drug taking and sexual activity.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2017/09/15/men-being-raped-at-chemsex-parties-are-too-afraid-to-go-to-the-police-6928504/|title=Men being raped at chemsex parties are too afraid to go to the police|date=2017-09-15|work=Metro|access-date=2018-06-16|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617015316/https://metro.co.uk/2017/09/15/men-being-raped-at-chemsex-parties-are-too-afraid-to-go-to-the-police-6928504/|archive-date=2018-06-17|url-status=live}}</ref> This included research into the prevalence of the practice and the negative impact on some men\u2019s lives.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.winq.com/2017/09/survey-gay-bi-men-reveals-shocking-truth-chemsex/|title=Survey of gay and bi men reveals the shocking truth about chemsex - winq.|date=2017-09-15|work=winq.|access-date=2018-06-16|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190105012424/http://www.winq.com/2017/09/survey-gay-bi-men-reveals-shocking-truth-chemsex/|archive-date=2019-01-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n[[Category:2011 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related media in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related websites]]\n[[Category:British news websites]]\n",