{"title_page": "Ang\u00e9lica Lagunas", "text_new": "'''Ang\u00e9lica Lagunas''' (born 26 May 1972) was a provincial deputy in [[Neuqu\u00e9n Province]] in Argentina.\n\nShe is a member of [[Socialist Left (Argentina)]] and was elected as a candidate of the [[Workers' Left Front]].\n\nShe held the post in rotation for a year, taking over from [[Ra\u00fal Godoy]] in December 2013, and handing over to [[Gabriela Suppicich]] in December 2014.\n\nShe previously worked as a [[school teacher]].\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.rionegro.com.ar/diario/juro-angelica-lagunas-como-diputada-del-fit-1425663-9701-nota.aspx article]\n*[https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=471923612918075 video] of her making her first speech in the provincial assembly\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lagunas, Angelica}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Socialist Left (Argentina) politicians]]\n[[Category:Argentine women in politics]]\n[[Category:People from Neuqu\u00e9n Province]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Argentine schoolteachers]]\n\n\n{{argentina-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Ang\u00e9lica Lagunas''' (born 26 May 1972) was a provincial deputy in [[Neuqu\u00e9n Province]] in Argentina.\n\nShe is a member of [[Socialist Left (Argentina)]] and was elected as a candidate of the [[Workers' Left Front]].\n\nShe held the post in rotation for a year, taking over from [[Ra\u00fal Godoy]] in December 2013, and handing over to [[Gabriela Suppicich]] in December 2014.\n\nShe previously worked as a [[school teacher]].\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.rionegro.com.ar/diario/juro-angelica-lagunas-como-diputada-del-fit-1425663-9701-nota.aspx article]\n*[https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=471923612918075 video] of her making her first speech in the provincial assembly\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lagunas, Angelica}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Socialist Left (Argentina) politicians]]\n[[Category:Argentine women in politics]]\n[[Category:People from Neuqu\u00e9n 